A parliamentary question tabled by the Tory MP Priti Patel shows that Labour ministers – including Andy Burnham, the party’s current health spokesman and former health secretary – received more than 1,500 warnings over the safety of care at the 14 hospitals on this “death list”, many from concerned staff, patients or members of the public. This includes more than 400 letters about the United Lincolnshire trust, and more than 300 about Blackpool.
